content:
Yesterday (04/1), there were ~711,600 new #COVID19 cases worldwide & ~11,900 deaths. 

Brazil saw the largest daily increase in cases worldwide (+91,097) followed by:

India (+81,466)
US (+79,029)
France (+50,455)
Turkey (+40,806)
Poland (+35,253)

https://t.co/HnLnwxAoXy https://t.co/Wz1v7B8Eff

content:
3️⃣The enduring appeal of extremist groups seems to lie in attending to fundamental human needs.

Important needs––for social bonds, for love/acceptance, to have a purpose in life––go unmet for some people. This can leave them prone to become involved with extremist views/groups.

Policymakers may face hurdles in enacting a vehicle miles traveled fee:

1️⃣Privacy concerns

RAND's Liisa Ecola and Laura Patton discuss how each could be addressed: https://t.co/qn0WyOuMcC
